<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (Euratom, ECSC, EEC) No 1307/87 of 11 May 1987 amending Council Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 300/76 determining the categories of officials entitled to allowances for shiftwork, and the rates and conditions thereof </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (Euratom, EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;) nr 1307/87, millega muudetakse n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rust (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 300/76, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks ametnike kategooriad, kellel on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml; eest, ning selle h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;rad ja maksmise tingimused 11. mai 1987 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Staff Regulations of Officials and the Conditions of Employment of Other Servants of the European Communities laid down in Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 259/68 (1), as last amended by Regulation (Euratom, ECSC, EEC) No 793/87 (2), and in particular the second subparagraph of Article 56a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike personalieeskirju ja &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimusi, mis on s&auml;testatud m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 259/68, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (Euratom, EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;) nr 793/87, (2) eelk&otilde;ige k&otilde;nealuste personalieeskirjade artikli 56a teist l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission made after consulting the Staff Regulations Committee, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse ettepanekut, mille komisjon esitas p&auml;rast n&otilde;upidamist personalieeskirjade komiteega, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas dispatch facilities for the Official Journal of the European Communities must be permanently available so that it can be distributed by the deadlines laid down; whereas, for one week in five, staff responsible for distribution work at night, including Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: selleks et Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajat saaks levitada etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaegade jooksul, peavad selle v&auml;ljastamisasutused t&ouml;&ouml;tama pidevalt; &uuml;hel n&auml;dalal viiest t&ouml;&ouml;tab levitamisega tegelev personal &ouml;&ouml;siti, seda ka laup&auml;eviti, p&uuml;hap&auml;eviti ja riigip&uuml;hadel; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 300/76 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 3856/86 (4), should therefore be extended to cover such staff, </inglise>
<eesti> m&auml;&auml;ruse (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 300/76 (3) (viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 3856/86 (4)) kohaldamisala tuleks seep&auml;rast laiendada nii, et see h&otilde;lmaks ka nimetatud t&ouml;&ouml;tajaid, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 (1) of Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 300/76 is hereby amended as follows: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 300/76 artikli 1 l&otilde;iget 1 muudetakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) The section of the first subparagraph following the words 'telex service', and preceding the indents, shall be replaced by the following: 'or involved in the dispatch of the Official Journal of the European Communities, who is engaged in shiftwork within the meaning of Article 56a of the Staff Regulations, shall be entitled to an allowance of: ' . </inglise>
<eesti> 1) esimeses l&otilde;igus lisatakse fraaside "teleksiteenuseid osutavas asutuses" ja "on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist:" vahele fraas "v&otilde;i tegeleb Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teataja v&auml;ljastamisega,". </eesti>
<inglise> (2) The following indent shall be inserted after the first indent: </inglise>
<eesti> 2) esimese taande j&auml;rele lisatakse j&auml;rgmine taane: </eesti>
<inglise> '- Bfrs 12 641 where the department operates on a two-shift basis, one of them at night, including Saturdays, Sundays and public holidays; ' . </inglise>
<eesti> "- 12 641 Belgia franki, kui t&ouml;&ouml; toimub kahes vahetuses, millest &uuml;ks on &ouml;ine, seda ka laup&auml;eviti, p&uuml;hap&auml;eviti ja riigip&uuml;hadel;". </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamisele j&auml;rgneval p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from the first day of the month following that in which it enters into force. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse selle j&otilde;ustumise kuule j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 11 May 1987. </inglise>
